---
title: Plant-Based Protein Messy Janes with Pickled Onion, Roasted Potato Wedges & Lime Aioli
description: Craving the ultimate throwback of the humble sloppy joe—minus the meat? Look no further. This version stars ground plant-based protein, and is worlds tastier than the ones the lunch lady slung: Think pickled onion, a smoky BBQ sauce, and a side of hearty potato wedges. (We’d definitely still recommend keeping a few napkins nearby, though.)
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/618be7302ff9ae5c026441d2-c381d827.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/plant-based-protein-messy-janes-618be7302ff9ae5c026441d2-ada9f585.pdf
cuisine: North America
time required: 30 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 880 kcal
  fat: 36 g
  saturated fat: 12 g
  carbohydrates: 118 g
  sugar: 37 g
  protein: 23 g
  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 1910 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/plant-based-protein-messy-janes-618be7302ff9ae5c026441d2
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @oil{}, @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. (You'll use the rest of the Southwest Spice later.)

Roast on top rack until lightly browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

While potatoes roast, halve, peel, and very thinly slice ¼ of the @Red Onion{1}; finely chop remaining. Quarter @Lime{1}. Halve @Brioche Buns{2}.

In a small #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine sliced onion, juice from half the lime, @Sugar{1/4%tsp}, and a pinch of salt. Microwave until onion is softened, ~{1%minute}. Set aside.

In a second small #bowl{}, combine @BBQ Sauce{4%tablespoon}, @Ketchup{2%tablespoon}, @Mushroom Stock Concentrate{1}, half the @Cornstarch{1%tablespoon}, remaining Southwest Spice, and @water{1%TBSP}.

In a third small bowl, combine @Mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} with a squeeze of lime juice. Season with salt.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chopped onion; cook, stirring, until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add @Ground Plant-Based Protein{6%ounce}; season with salt and pepper. Using a #spatula{}, press into an even layer; cook, undisturbed, until browned on bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Break up protein into pieces and continue cooking until browned all over and warmed through, ~{3-4%minutes} more.

Add @water{2%TBSP} to pan with plant-based protein, then stir in BBQ sauce mixture. Cook, stirring, until sauce has thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: If sauce seems too thick, stir in another splash of water.

Taste and season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat.

Meanwhile, toast buns until golden brown.

Divide buns between plates; spread cut sides of bottom buns with lime mayo. Fill buns with messy jane filling and as much pickled onion (draining first) as you like.

Serve with potato wedges on the side and any remaining lime mayo for dipping.